verses.roman:
ei mora manera kathā keha nāhi jāne
sabe bale, kene āilā rāma-keli-grāme

synonyms: ei—this; mora—My; manera—of the mind; kathā—intentions; keha—anyone; nāhi—not; jāne—knows; sabe—everyone; bale—says; kene—why; āilā—You came; rāmakeli-grāme—to this village named Rāmakeli.
translation: "Everyone is asking why I have come to this village of Rāmakeli. No one knows My intentions.
